longest_values: Docks were not registering returned bikes for a 15 minute period.  Some docks made no noise with no lights, other docks made grinding noise with long yellow light and then the bike would still be unlocked.Someone was returning a bike and very angry that the station wasnt working. He docked bike 07216 at dock 11. Grinding noise, yellow light but no green light. The bike is locked now.

Sixth dock from end of station had yellow light when I arrived at station. I inserted my inspection key to redock it and test if light would go away. One beep sounded, the light stayed yellow, and then the dock beeped continuously for about two minutes. The yellow light is no longer on.

Dock 3 had remnants of blue tape covering cassette but had been flattened into cassette. I tried to dock a bike, the dock made a grinding noise but the bike did not dock. The yellow light was on formore than two minutes but has turned off.  I locked bike at adjacent dock.

One dock had tape ripped off cassette although station is not available.  I tried my bike and was able to redock. The green light turned on  and my bike was locked.  I could not check out the bike again with my member key or inspection key.

Map printed incorrectly.  Depicts 7th Ave traffic as running uptown, states Penn Station is located downtown from station location when it is uptown. Also depicts 8th Ave where 6th Ave should be and vice versa.
